<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-275-282  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 275 282.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Feb 27 1989 v3 n9 pS2(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AWIPS-90: heart, soul and brains of a weather-forecasting system.andO;(Advanced Weather Interactive Processing System for the 1990s)(System Views: A Supplement to Computer Week)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Anthes, Gary H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Weather Service's (NWS) AWIPS-90 system will be anon-going, automated integrator of systems that support NWS'weather forecasting beyond the mid-1990s.andP;  Systems that will feeddata to AWIPS include the Next-Generation Weather Radar, theAutomated Surface Observation Systems (ASOS) program, the TwoGeostationary Operational Environmental Satellites (GOES) and theAtmospheric Profilers.andP;  In addition, AWIPS will also receivemeteorological and hydrological data from other NWS sites.andP;  AWIPSand its systems are designed to provide accurate, localized andtimely mesoscale forecasts - predictions that cover fast breakingevents.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MeteorologyUnited States. National Weather ServiceInformation SystemsInteractive SystemsGovernment AgencyGoals and Objectives.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>